{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease and line base of a round cake tin (Ø 20 cm) with baking paper.","Place chillies, garlic and coriander in mixing bowl then mince <nobr>3 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add semolina, yoghurt, 120 g water, salt and bicarbonate of soda then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared cake tin.","Place remaining 1000 g water in mixing bowl and place Varoma dish into position. Arrange 2 wooden skewers, cut to fit (approx. 19 cm), in Varoma dish. Rest cake tin on top of skewers ensuring it is level then cover and steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Set Varoma aside and remove Varoma lid then allow to stand for 3 minutes before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["½ tsp vegetable oil, for greasing","2 fresh green chillies, halved","2 garlic cloves","15 g fresh coriander leaves","150 g semolina","180 g plain yoghurt","1120 g water","1 tsp fine sea salt","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda"]}],"id":"r111575","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-OfMguY6CRtA\/XZMwGj-P_EI\/AAAAAAAAaZw\/WfhuhxeXTEkQ4f2YypOaOyO-TFT85Fa0gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wI_W0Z1xvLiN7vv8.png","title":"Dhokla","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.8 g","fat":"1.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11.7 g","calories":"282 kJ \/ 68 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, wooden skewers","hintsAndTricks":["This light, fluffy, savoury steamed cake is incredibly versatile and can be served as a snack, starter or side dish. Originating in Gujarat, it is traditionally made with rice and lentils but this quick version uses semolina and is known in the west as ‘instant’ dhokla.","Using wooden skewers in the base of the Varoma dish creates a trivet for the cake tin to stand on. This enables the steam to circulate evenly around the tin without any obstructions.","Serve with pickles or chutneys and salad or as an accompaniment to curries.","Can be served warm or at room temperature."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","30m","10 portions"]}